This paper is about a deep reinforcement learning approach to a multi-agent domain, which involves challenges such as partial observability, decentralized execution, and sparse and delayed rewards. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), which are the main areas of research for deep reinforcement learning. Additionally, the paper involves game theory (cs.GT), multi-agent systems (cs.MA), and robotics (cs.RO), which are also relevant sub-categories for this work.
